messages.content: ComfyUI-SizeFromArray is a custom node for ComfyUI that outputs a random pair of width and height from a given array.
To install ComfyUI-SizeFromArray, navigate to the custom_nodes directory within your ComfyUI installation and run the command: git clone https://github.com/ITurchenko/ComfyUI-SizeFromArray.git
What does the ComfyUI-SizeFromArray node do?
The ComfyUI-SizeFromArray node takes an array of width and height pairs as input and outputs a randomly selected pair from the array.
No, ComfyUI-SizeFromArray is a custom node that extends the functionality of ComfyUI, which is a GUI tool for generating images and videos using stable diffusion models.
Can I customize the array of width and height pairs in ComfyUI-SizeFromArray?
Yes, you can customize the array of width and height pairs that the ComfyUI-SizeFromArray node uses to output a random size.
Does ComfyUI-SizeFromArray require any additional dependencies?
The provided documentation does not mention any additional dependencies required for ComfyUI-SizeFromArray beyond the standard ComfyUI installation.
Is there a preview image available for ComfyUI-SizeFromArray?
Yes, the documentation includes a preview image named 'example.png' that demonstrates the functionality of the ComfyUI-SizeFromArray node.
